website_summaries.verdict: An affordable and healthy option for dogs in any stage of their life.
pros: Full of helpful nutrients suitable for young, old, or pregnant dogs
Reduces gas and contributes to a shiny, healthy coat of fur
cons: Food has a rather strong scent

customer_reviews.title: Dogs are very sick after eating this food.
customer_reviews.text: We have two dogs who have been having diarrhea and vomiting since opening this current bag of dog food. We have a third dog who has stopped eating the dog food, aside from trying to find food from other sources (not usually a problem) and is completely healthy. We've used this brand for a while and have a subscription, but are very concerned about our dogs health. We just ran over to Walmart today to buy different food for them. We'd hate to have to do an emergency vet visit on the 4th of July, but we may have to.
customer_reviews.author: Blipoo

customer_reviews.title: Rich Kibble
customer_reviews.text: Our pup's breeder weans her litters onto this food. My goal was to keep him on this but it had turned out to not be a good fit for him, or us (it's an incredibly stinky food). He constantly had gas, dark (the color of the kibble) rancid smelling feces, loose/soft stool, and he just didn't like it... to the point that a 9 week old puppy was turning his nose up to food. He was vetted, as we were concerned, but it's just not a good kibble for us. We have since moved him to a different brand and he's doing great- even with the switch.
customer_reviews.author: M.B

customer_reviews.title: I only reccomend this if your dog was raised from a puppy on it
customer_reviews.text: If you raised your puppy on this then it should be fine. A breeder told me he uses it to keep his hunting beagles weight under control and it improves their coat. For that puppy it seemed ok. He didn't eat much and he was tiny. For our other puppy it was a fail. He hated it so much he would go without eating. Overall I'd say its not something either dog loved. I wont purchase this again.
customer_reviews.author: Star

customer_reviews.title: Well-Respected Kibble
customer_reviews.text: We ordered the Hi-Pro Plus because our breeder used it to feed our puppy before she arrived. She is doing well on it, and our in-the-know show dog expert says it is a staple in the show world.
customer_reviews.author: Fireflyfaster

customer_reviews.title: 100% Better Than Taste of the Wild!
customer_reviews.text: My dog is a picky dog eater and she grazes on throughout the day, well at least she did with Taste of the Wild. After finding out that my dog throwing up multiple times a day was because of the food, I switched to Victor immediately because it has no recalls and other German Shorthaired Pointer owners rave about it. She loves this stuff and hasn’t thrown up since I switched! This is our second bag!
customer_reviews.author: Kimberly Harrold-Lewis

customer_reviews.title: Excellent
customer_reviews.text: Excellent . My pups is 5 months old and has bulked up very nicely. Still has a lot of growing to do but the food has helped a lot.
customer_reviews.author: Kevin Rivera

customer_reviews.title: Recipe changed and now it gives my dog diarrhea.
customer_reviews.text: After my last shipment of Victor Classic - Hi-Pro Plus, my dog started getting diarrhea that never seemed to go away. I ran some tests with his vet and determined that the dog food was the cause. He has been eating this food exclusively since he was able to eat kibble but unfortunately we now have to make a switch. I will not be buying this brand anymore.
customer_reviews.author: Ethan Pursley

customer_reviews.title: Horrible dog food....This food made my dog really sick
customer_reviews.text: I bought this dog food for my standard poodle. He ate this food couple of times. Each time he ate it, he got really sick and started vomiting, never mind the over $175.00 vet checkup and medicine because of this food. I changed this food to another brand and he is doing well now. I asked the seller if I can return this product, and they are asking for 15% re-stocking fee for something that makes dogs sick. I'm not sure why is amazon selling this product without testing it. Be aware this product!
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Changed ingredients
customer_reviews.text: Disappointed now that they changed the ingredients and added blood meal. Made all 3 of my dogs very sick and they thrived on this prior to ingredients change.
customer_reviews.author: Soccerfan

customer_reviews.title: Check your sizes
customer_reviews.text: The price of the 5 lb bag was $7 less than Chewys! The larger sizes are much more expensive than Chewys thouh. This is kind of strange. Our 1 1/2 year old Doxie has been on it since she has been weened and likes it very much. My advice to anybody is buy a good brand of food and if your dog likes it stick with it forever! We mix in some meat for her at dinner time too. Obviously if your dog has some problems like diarrhea or very soft stools you might have to try another brand but you can buy this with confidence that this is a good product.
customer_reviews.author: Popper

customer_reviews.title: My dogs love this food
customer_reviews.text: I have 4 dogs. They all LOVE this Victors food. I got it because the breeder of my puppy feeds it. I let my 3 older dogs try some and now they eat like I e never seen!! One of my dogs is a 3 pound Chihuahua who is picky. She gobbles this stuff down. I’ve been feeding this for 2 mos now, it seems to agree with everyone, and they all look great.
customer_reviews.author: C. Stone

customer_reviews.title: Finally...
customer_reviews.text: ... after trying MANY different brands for my Great Dane puppy over the course of 9 months, someone in a Facebook group suggested Victor. She likes it (and by now she IS a connoisseur)...but more importantly, it's the first food that has given her a solid poop! I never thought I'd be so thrilled to see a turd the size of a log, but yay! She's been eating this food for over two months now and going strong.
customer_reviews.author: PrncssBhm

customer_reviews.title: Big NO NO for my Baby 🐕
customer_reviews.text: I hate giving bad reviews but i also hate that my baby doent want to eat it any more and its giving him Alergy i was reading all the comments abouth somthing diffrent with the formula i dint want to believe it and i still got it for him but now i have started to see the changes on his skin and his hair it falling he is scratching alot and he does not want to eat it any more... am sorry but this is no good for my baby any more 😞
customer_reviews.author: Alejandra Reyes

customer_reviews.title: No more itching or fleas
customer_reviews.text: OK! Lots to share with you! My vet informed me about dangers of PEA protein in dog food- causes heart disease in dogs. Placed my dog in this product/Victor Classic- (which is PEA protein Free), and I’m actually saving money!!! I noticed he is hardly scratching, do not have to use flea medication And his fur is a lot thicker, this is no joke. I love love this product. Our Great Dane mix seems to love it too. Oh and our Dachund mix also has no more periodic hives or itching. Fantastic company.
customer_reviews.author: Haber

customer_reviews.title: Rates high on dogfoodadvisor.com
customer_reviews.text: I often check dogfoodadvisor.com to make sure I feed my dogs good quality food. This came rated 4-5 stars. My dogs eat wet mixed with dry and of course prefer wet. This isn't their favorite but they do eat it which is good. It is higher priced than some dry foods but it is worth it knowing you are feeding your dogs quality ingredients which will help them live longer.
customer_reviews.author: Rebecca Green

customer_reviews.title: Excellent food we moved all our dogs too it.
customer_reviews.text: I have been feeding my dog Eukanuba their whole lives recently we got a puppy & the puppy was already eating this food. I did a lot studying exactly what ingredients is in this food and I have to say this is really Good food. We are dog trainers we have a business train service dogs for disabled people I am paralyzed wheelchair-bound. We will be Changing and all 4,dogs of ours will be on this food! Although it would be very nice from this company if they would be willing to work with us price-wise considering that we will be buying numerous bags..
customer_reviews.author: Im,late

customer_reviews.title: Safe, healthy, happy dog!
customer_reviews.text: My dachshund Moose was on Blue Buffalo for awhile but we decided to take him off grain free food and try something new. I was nervous because he has a sensitive stomach and he's never been too excited about eating so it really needs to be good for him to eat his meals. I was overwhelmed by the choices of dog food and how many people claimed theirs was 'healthy' or 'natural'. I never thought I'd choose a brand I'd never heard of before, but after reading the ingredients list and seeing that it was formulated to meet the nutritional levels established by the AAFCO, I went for it. Moose never skips a meal now and he's healthier than ever!
customer_reviews.author: Jessie M

customer_reviews.title: Recommend
customer_reviews.text: I believe this product is much better for my dog then Purina. I wish my dog would eat it without canned food, but I got her from a shelter and she is used to can, so I mix a little victor can food with the dry. Only reason four stars is I was hoping it would tasted good enough for our dog to eat without can food mixed in. Using this more expensive food, because of all the things that I have read about grain and unhealthy big name brand foods.
customer_reviews.author: kyle

customer_reviews.title: Love it buy it
customer_reviews.text: Love it love it . Should’ve been feeding dogs this . Would’ve had a full kennel by now . I been feeding science diet because dog tend use the bathroom with but wasn’t as thick as I wanted my five month bully xl to be and he would still be hungry with science diet . With being on victor for only three days I can tell he’s putting on weight rapidly and used the bathroom only once a day . He was also sick when I intially ordered victor n was on rice n chicken . Idk what victor got in it but after third feed of victor everything was back to normal .
customer_reviews.author: Tee

customer_reviews.title: Highly recommend!
customer_reviews.text: I’ve seen big improvements in my Aussie/English shepherd mix. I made the switch to this post after the FDA released data of grain free foods with lentils, chickpeas, etc. I made the mistake of transitioning too fast because I ran out of his old food. Once his body transitioned, I’ve seen a big change. His coat is shinier, and he seems more lively. The food is very nutrient dense, therefore he eats less and poops less. However, his energy has doubled! Per pound it’s a lot cheaper than the other brands I’ve tried and the ingredients are better!
customer_reviews.author: Cody Glaze

customer_reviews.title: Found cheaper at Local Hardware store
customer_reviews.text: Great dog food. Found it at my local hardware store for $10 cheaper. My dogs BM are much more consistent since switching from Pedigree, a male & a female border collie. Solid stools from hipro plus. pedigree, blue Buffalo, and science diet all gave my doggos loose & watery stools. Energy is high, coats are beautiful and shiny.
customer_reviews.author: Shiv

customer_reviews.title: Can’t buy in store but totally worth it
customer_reviews.text: My puppy loves this dog food! He was feed this at the breeder and I continued to give him the same. If you look up the food like I did you will see that it’s one of the only brands to never have a recall. My pup will beg for his food and eats it like he eats his treats. This is a great brand for bully breeds and blue nose dogs. I have not had any issues with his coat that happens to blue nose breeds.
customer_reviews.author: Chrisssiey

customer_reviews.title: Top shelf dog food without the premium price tag.
customer_reviews.text: Feed 2 very active, athletic dogs this food, along with an older retired one. They love it and do very well on it. Their poop is relatively small and very firm, which indicates to me that the food is digestible and efficient. Lovely coats, shiny eyes and energy through the roof. Look at the ingredients and research the manufacturer. Victor sources their high-quality ingredients close to home wherever possible (their plant is in Texas). 88% of the protein is from high quality animal sources. Good stuff.
customer_reviews.author: J. Richter

customer_reviews.title: Excellent, both pup and parents are happy
customer_reviews.text: Very good food, and my pup loves it. He was on Pro plan from breeder bit I wanted to get him off the food due to corn in the food. Switched to Victor and he isn't itching like he used to and he really likes it. Less mess in yard and easier to pick up too! Top quality, and they use meat meals so there is more meat vs others with meat and moisture cooked out. I like that is has probiotics in it as well. Give it a try with their small bags first and see.
customer_reviews.author: happycamper

customer_reviews.title: Grain-free dog food studies say your dogs need some grain in their food!
customer_reviews.text: Recent studies of grain-free dog food show a connection between grain-free foods and heart trouble in dogs. Do your dog and yourself a favor and switch to a high quality kibble that includes at least some grain in it. This food is highly recommended by the non-profit Dog Food Advisor website. Check it out. And, our dogs like it quite a bit.
customer_reviews.author: Amazo

customer_reviews.title: High quality great food
customer_reviews.text: Not sure what the naysayers are complaining about, just switched my beloved springer spaniel with a heart condition to this food to get away fro the grain free formulas. He wolfs this food down. And, in fact, to me it smells great, I'd eat it! He loved Orijin original, but he loves this even more. He won't touch Eagle Pack. He's doing great on it. It makes him happy. It's good for his heart. Great food. And economical to boot!
customer_reviews.author: Vermonter

customer_reviews.title: Put weight back on my dog, great ingredients
customer_reviews.text: The kibble that we had been using changed to pea flour and pea protein. My giant breed dog became very ill on it vomiting constantly. He went from 140 lbs to 119 lbs. I searched far and wide for a high protein kibble that contained no legumes. This product proved to be excellent. He gained weight back to 133 lbs and looks great, is full of energy, and has a beautiful coat. The auto ship has made it so easy to keep a dog food supply for our 2 dogs during coronavirus quarantine.
customer_reviews.author: Foresthome

customer_reviews.title: Dogs have more energy and aren’t stiff in the morning after three days
customer_reviews.text: Dogs are looking better. Way more energy. Not stiff in the mornings. Unlike blue buffalo they clean this up fast. The blue buffalo they would eat half then slowly eat the rest throughout the day. This just seemed to be a next level dog food.
customer_reviews.author: Matt

customer_reviews.title: First dog food my dachshund ever really liked!
customer_reviews.text: My dog has a sensitive stomach and also isn't interested in food in general. I used to have to make him eat once a day because I'd feed him breakfast and dinner and he'd wait a day and a half and finally eat. All he wants to do is play, he didn't really care about food. I switched him to this and it was the first time I watched him drop his ball and walk over and eat. And he finishes every time. It's seriously made a difference.
customer_reviews.author: Jessie M

customer_reviews.title: dog's OK with it
customer_reviews.text: I have spoiled dogs,. I've done raw, they wanted it cooked. They would swallow huge hunks of raw bone, so I chickened out and started grinding it. I can't always manage 100% homemade and I worrying about the vitamins, etc. so I use some kibble. They turned their noses up at many brands, even the most expensive. They always eat every bit of this kibble.
customer_reviews.author: Marguerite C. Thibeau

customer_reviews.title: Our dogs love this food
customer_reviews.text: Our dogs love this food. Expensive, but high quality food is just going to be. They have shiny coats and they’re in good health, which has partially to with quality food like this one. They’ve had others but when we come back to this one they are always happy to smell it in their bowl and they gobble it.
customer_reviews.author: Allen

customer_reviews.title: Five Stars
customer_reviews.text: My 6mo bully puppy loves this premium dog food, will definitely be buying again. He's doing great on it, I've been feeding this food since he was 12wks old
customer_reviews.author: Rkn2903

customer_reviews.title: ... a year now and our Aussie puppy is growing wonderfully. He has a great coat and he's at ...
customer_reviews.text: We've been using this dog food for almost a year now and our Aussie puppy is growing wonderfully. He has a great coat and he's at a good weight. He's a very active, happy puppy and loves to play all the time. I've never used any other dog food since this is what the breeder recommended and he's liked it. We put some warm water on it or low fat broth occasionally, making it a little soft and crunchy at the same time.
customer_reviews.author: JCinVA

customer_reviews.title: Don't give the dog too much!
customer_reviews.text: This is some very rich dog food. I feed my 45 lbs dog the recommended amount for a 20 lb dog and he maintains weight. He is pretty active. He is hungry a lot and a big begger for food scraps. Probably a better choice for an extremely active dog or one with a very high metabolism. It would be great for a farm dog, for example. The plus side is that one bag lasts a really long time, so it's actually very cheap.
customer_reviews.author: Thomas

customer_reviews.title: Turns white dogs mouth and bottoms rusty brown
customer_reviews.text: My 2 white Goldendoodles like this food and I feel it is a quality product. However my white dogs mouth and bottoms have turned a rusty brown color since eating this. I called the Victor company for help and all they told me is that no dye is used in this formula. So, apparently it is a mystery as to the discoloration. Unfortunately I will not continue to purchase for this reason.
customer_reviews.author: Love2travel

customer_reviews.title: I know this food is recommended but made my dog deathly ill.
customer_reviews.text: Was using as a supplement to my dogs regular food. She became so ill, throwing up, lethargic - I was almost to the point of rushing her to emergency vet. I started giving her her regular food and she was back to her normal happy self in one day.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Great dog food!
customer_reviews.text: For the longest time I had my two pups on Blue Buffalo limited ingredients & large puppy formula. Both dogs either had upset stomachs or bathroom issues until I switched to Victor's. They love this food and eat it up right away! Now they don't have any stomach or bathroom issues and twirl every time they hear me fill up their bowls! So glad I tried this brand after reading about it on Dog Food Advisor.
customer_reviews.author: Amanda Davila

customer_reviews.title: Unbelievably horrible
customer_reviews.text: I bought a 40lb bag of this food that will be throw away. This food has torn my lil 10 week old baby's tummy up. Constant explosive diarrhea, losing weight and vet visit. The smell is so horrible....it smells like death. There is now blood in his poop. Whatever the company did to change the ingredients.....don't risk it!!!
customer_reviews.author: Chad

customer_reviews.title: Great Kibble
customer_reviews.text: Good quality food at a good cost. When I first got my lab, he had terrible gas constantly. Previous owner was feeding him cheap foods. After a brief adjustment to Victor, thats a thing of the past and solid poop. Been on this food for 2 months now and no plans to change that. Not sure why the reviews about loose stools etc. This is a quality product.
customer_reviews.author: Justin M. Wallace

customer_reviews.title: Absolutely Best Dog Food On Market!
customer_reviews.text: This is by far the best dog food for large breed puppies or dogs. All ingredients are pure. Changed our 7 month old German Short Haired Pointer from the Purina Pro Plan Focus to this and he has completely calmed down. Before, he was so wired and couldn't get him to pay attention at all. Now, how behavior is completely different; very calm yet attentive. And his muscle definition is gorgeous.
customer_reviews.author: Michelle Hargenrader

customer_reviews.title: High quality food for my Dog!
customer_reviews.text: My dog is loving it and we are too! Knowing that he is getting the best quality of food and the nutrients he needs, makes us happy and it’s good quality food. The food is pricey, I am not going to lie, but it’s well worth it. Not full of fillers like most cheaper dog food out there. A great investment in his food now, will lead to a healthy dog in the long run.
customer_reviews.author: Jojo

customer_reviews.title: Great for muscle mass. Not so good for sensetive breeds
customer_reviews.text: My American bully liked this for the first few weeks and gained a lot of muscle mass. I got the second bag and she immediately started avoiding her food. A few days went by and she started having allergic reactions. Not sure if I got a bad batch but this seems to be a common occurrence with repeat orders. Also depends on your dogs tolerance to certain meats or veggies.
customer_reviews.author: A.A

customer_reviews.title: Best food on the market
customer_reviews.text: I am very selective with what I feed my dogs. They dont get table scraps and only get dry food so I wanted to ensure a balanced diet. They are super active and about 5olbs and eat 3-4 cups per day. The vet always says they are super healthy. The dogs also absolutely love this food! Do your research and you will see this is amazing food and a an amazing price as well.
customer_reviews.author: Hunter Freeman

customer_reviews.title: Doggie approved.  Kinda.
customer_reviews.text: Preference in these things is similar to that with people. One dog loves it, another dog hates it. So i can only speak for my dog. She likes it, she isnt crazy about it, but she likes it better than most dog foods. I usually mix it with some wet dog food and she likes it better that way, though she will eat it plain.
customer_reviews.author: InfidelUberAlles

customer_reviews.title: So far so good
customer_reviews.text: Decent size bag for 20$ I bought this specifically to see bulking up of my pup he’s fairly thin. My American bully pup was very eager to try sticking his nose in the bag and sneezing a few in lol. He liked them so initial reaction was great. Waiting on him to go potty to check will update with any vomiting or diarrhea. (Specifically keeping an eye on bulking up pup!)
customer_reviews.author: Adrian

customer_reviews.title: Best dog food
customer_reviews.text: I changed to Victor after a friend recommended it. After reading the list of ingredients and nutritional requirements, I decided to give it a try. I suggest following the feeding instructions, when changing the brand of any dog food. Slowly introducing new food by mixing with their existing food , gives their tummy a chance to digest the new food with out distruping their digestive system.
customer_reviews.author: Live2Love

customer_reviews.title: Good product.
customer_reviews.text: Dogs are not excited about the flavor, but then, of course they loved the junk food i was giving them before. Unlike most people, I don't freak out when my dogs don't eat right away. They will eventually eat it if they are hungry. Just let them get used to the flavor. Kids love Mac and Cheese, but won't touch their brocolli or spinach. Thats how I take it.
customer_reviews.author: Joseph

customer_reviews.title: My dog is Doing great on this!
customer_reviews.text: I ordered this dog food as a substitution for the Royal Canine Hi Protein dog good; due to the expensiveness. My pup is going great and loves the taste. I do notice her poo is a lot darker. I presume that is normal. I have a Great Dane, 10 months.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Very happy dog and humom!
customer_reviews.text: We used to get Costco brand dog food until we realized that this was the same exact price but better ingredients. My dog LOVES it and gets excited to eat it! It makes her fur super soft and she gets less diarrhea. It is for active dogs though so beware because I think it could easily make a lazy dog fat. Haha
customer_reviews.author: Valerie

customer_reviews.title: Affordable
customer_reviews.text: I switched my Siberian huskies to victors since I wanted a big bag of quality food for an affordable price. I’ve tried other brands and they always have watery poop. This is great because I can buy different flavors and they do great on it. We recently just had a liter of puppies and I put them on this food. They’ve done great and had healthy poop. They love it!! I will always buy this brand!!!
customer_reviews.author: Kelsey Van Natter

customer_reviews.title: Excellent food!
customer_reviews.text: This was highly recommended by our dog's breeder, who spends a fair amount of time researching the best and most healthy foods for dogs. The Victor Hi-Pro Plus was her Number One recommendation! Our dog loves it!
customer_reviews.author: LCSteve

customer_reviews.title: 3 happy healthy dogs!
customer_reviews.text: When I got my 3rd poodle the breeder told me this was her go to. So, I bought a bag. All three loved it! My oldest poodle can’t eat anything without getting sick really bad sick! But he tolerates this food very well! They have all been on it for 3 years and I will never change their food again.
customer_reviews.author: KRash

customer_reviews.title: Shipped in original packaging
customer_reviews.text: Only complaint here is that due to not being boxed up, size, weight and shippers, I’ve had about 3 bags come in with small holes on it. But it is a big 50 lb bag of dog food. The 40 lb bag is boxed up for shipping - but my dogs (XL American Bullies) go through too much to order 40 lb bags.

customer_reviews.title: It is a good product for dogs- just not mine
customer_reviews.text: Great product- just didn’t sit well with my puppy. All dogs are different so I returned. Amazon graciously refunded- and we have donated to a dog shelter. customer_reviews.text: They changed the formula for the worse. Blood meal, vegetable oil and cellulose powder are new or replacements for better ingredients. I'll be looking for something new now, again...

customer_reviews.title: Top quality.  Very recommended
customer_reviews.text: Fantastic top quality food Highly recommended. Very nutritious dense food. Feed less than lower quality foods. Dogs love taste. AFCO approved food. All stages of life. Feeding instructions and advice on bag is the best I have seen. Main protein source is meat
customer_reviews.author: Kyle

customer_reviews.title: Healthy and Safe dog food
customer_reviews.text: Very good dog food with Selenium Yeast instead of the chemical Sodium Selenite. You never want that chemical in your dogs' food or treats. Can create problems in their blood, etc. Victor was created by two men that seem to really care about their product and I am impressed after researching for years to find the safest food to feed my furkids.

customer_reviews.title: Great dog food, just accidentally was open when it got delivered
customer_reviews.text: The bag came open and dog food out in the box. I will not give low star due to fact of someThing going wrong, because my dogs love this dog food and it’s great food to feed my pitbulls with their raw diets Love victor
customer_reviews.author: Joseph Legacy II

customer_reviews.title: Great for dogs digestion
customer_reviews.text: After searching for three years for a product my dog could process in a solid manner I found Victor. No more loose stools. He likes it and since he likes any food I can not comment on the flavor. After all he eats seashells. All I know is he is on a solid footing.
customer_reviews.author: Dwight L. Davis

customer_reviews.title: Great dog food
customer_reviews.text: Puppy had a thin coat until I started feeding her Victor, now it is thick and shiny. The breeder had her eating an expensive boutique brand that didn't seem to do anything for her coat and she didn't like the flavor the way she does Victor.

customer_reviews.title: Formula changed

customer_reviews.author: TK

customer_reviews.title: Pit bull
customer_reviews.text: Love it love it . Put the weight I was looking for on my dog in less then two weeks ( I also do DYNE and a little raw ground beef once a dog . Pit bull

customer_reviews.title: My dogs love this food!

I also love that it comes in a 40 lb bag so I don’t have to order as much. For both dogs I feed a total of about 4 cups per day this bag will last me over a month. Their poops have been smaller and solid too! I recommend this food to everyone!

customer_reviews.title: Not a Favorite

customer_reviews.author: Noelle

customer_reviews.title: Beware do not buy
customer_reviews.text: This was the food the Breeder told me she had my puppy on. Not sure if I got a bad bag but it gave my dog a stomach ache and diarrhea and she dropped weight. Changed to a different brand dog food and immediately stopped the issue. Would not buy or recommend. Local feed store said they quit selling due to this very issue.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Switched from TotW and never looked back!
customer_reviews.text: The kibble is always consistent in size, shape and smell. I definitely can't speak on the taste but the dogs always enjoy! 40lbs is quite heavy but we manage with a large rolling container. We switch over to this dog food after having my dog on Taste of the Wild. But unfortunately TotW had some serious issues with heart disease in dogs. So we made the switch and haven't looked back!
customer_reviews.author: Anila Arif

customer_reviews.title: High quality
customer_reviews.text: My dog does amazing on this food. He has a super sensitive stomach, but this really helps.
customer_reviews.author: stephanie

customer_reviews.title: Great Food.  Good Price.
customer_reviews.text: My dogs love, I mean REALLY love this food. I like it because it keeps their poops well formed and small. We’ve had problems with other food causing itching or loose stools, but that’s not the case with this food. My boys have silky soft coats and seem really happy.
customer_reviews.author: Florida Mom

customer_reviews.title: My German Shepherd loves it
customer_reviews.text: Change over from Nutrisource food to this after some FDA issues about dog foods My dog loves it and due to him being a free eater I want the best I can for him. The other brand has made issue of the dog health and I switched to this and glad I did well worth the money
customer_reviews.author: john west

customer_reviews.title: Made my dogs sick
customer_reviews.text: Unfortunately something has changed with this dog food. First bag went great, second one both of my dogs started refusing to eat it almost immediately. One of them got sick and refused to eat anything at all except plain chicken. She was sick for several days,we had to make homemade dog food for them to get them to eat again and now they are both eating again, so it was definitely that food. Unfortunately for me I didnt think of trying to return it until I read reviews with the same problem. $50 out the window and it made my dogs sick.
customer_reviews.author: KELLI TWISS

customer_reviews.title: Dry Stool/ Upset Stomach
customer_reviews.text: I read reviews online and read the reviews on amazon. I was bought on the amount you get for the price. You usually get half the amount for the same price but unfortunately my dogs aren’t doing that well on it. Their stool comes out dry and hard. I was thinking they just needed more time to adjust but no. My dogs had a hard time pushing their stool out because of this food. Upset stomach and my dog started eating grass as of recently. Won’t be buying this food again. Thanks
customer_reviews.author: Esteve C.

customer_reviews.title: Something is WRONG with this bag of dog food!!
customer_reviews.text: I have used Victor dog food for a while now but this bag...something is wrong with it. I own 3 toy sized schnauzers. All 3 of them sniff it and dump it out and refuse to eat it. I’ve tried over and over to get them to eat it to no avail. Something is wrong!
customer_reviews.author: Sheryle L Phillips

customer_reviews.title: Dogs don’t like but momma does!
customer_reviews.text: My dogs don’t seem to care for the taste of this food. I have to mix it with another brand to get them to eat it. I’ve tried most of the flavors. I have noticed that when they’re on this food, they look like they have more meat on their bones. I’ve switched the brand before and their ribs start to show and I have to give them a lot more food. I’m happy with this food even though it’s not my dogs favorite. I have 2 Great Danes. Both under 2yrs and they’ve been on this good for about 1.5yrs.
customer_reviews.author: christian hinojosa

customer_reviews.title: May make your dog sick
customer_reviews.text: I’m so disappointed in this dog food. We have been ordering this food for over a year and had no problems, but we recently got a new bag and our dog kept throwing up after eating and having diarreah. We found out it’s because they switched their ingredients. So disappointed that we had not been told their ingredients changed. I just bought a brand new bag and can not get a Refund. Complete waste of 50 dollars.
customer_reviews.author: Lauren McGee

customer_reviews.title: No regrets at all for me and my GSD
customer_reviews.text: My GSD was pooping mustard diarrhea. His stools were coming out soggy and watery. She was barely eating. A friend from the dog park recommended me this and 2 days after I've given her this product her poops were coming out dark, smaller and sturdier! She loves it. Now she eats a ton more and seems with more energy. If you want your dog to be healthier and not have stomach problems this is the best food!
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: No issues
customer_reviews.text: Have been getting this food from the being of owning my pup. She had done well on it and haven't any diarrhea, my other dog switched over and she hasn't had any issues. I see some people's dogs haven't reacted well and each dog is specific to how they react to different dog food.
customer_reviews.author: No Name

customer_reviews.title: Overpriced and Over-rated
customer_reviews.text: Bought high protein for my Hybrid wolf dog and she wouldn't touch it. No would rather starve and she almost did.
customer_reviews.author: #27 sucks!

customer_reviews.title: One of the best all around!
customer_reviews.text: We feed our dogs nothing but victor dog food from day one and they love! We have now 5 dogs and we would foster dogs also and all of them have liked it. We would switch them to this and their stools would firm up.
customer_reviews.author: Ray Guinto

customer_reviews.title: Shiny coat
customer_reviews.text: Our breeder started our puppy on Victor after weening. We continued Victor and noticed how beautiful and shiny our puppy’s coat was. After a bout of sickness, our vet changed her dog food to a different brand (one that he sells🤦🏻‍♀️), and her coat lost its luster within a week. We are transitioning her back to Victor, and her coat is already starting to change again.
customer_reviews.author: CQ

customer_reviews.title: Keeps My Puppy Peppy!
customer_reviews.text: I’m taking my dog’s opinion on the flavor. He loves it. This food is what his breeder had him on and was highly recommended from other sources. It’s hard to find in stores, but Amazon makes it super simple to keep him in Supply. The only downfall is that with it being dogfood, ants can detect and will swarm it if left on your porch too long. Be careful if this when bringing the box inside the house. I usually open the box outside and bring only the bag inside after wiping any ants off.
customer_reviews.author: Brittany

customer_reviews.title: Victor has all the ingredients in a food that a dog needs...
customer_reviews.text: I got a new puppy and the breeder recommended Victor I gave it to her for 5 months and all of a sudden she started with diarrhea... The vet recommended I change her food to pro plan puppy and not to long after her diarrhea went away... Not sure if the Victor was becoming to rich for her or not... I still recommend this dog food I’m not sure what gave my pup diarrhea...It’s a quality dog food...
customer_reviews.author: Bonnie Titus

customer_reviews.title: Great Product
customer_reviews.text: We have a GSD with pancreatic insufficiency whose digestive system is very fragile. We needed a low (<4%) fiber kibble to aid her digestion. After having been through 4 brands of kibble, we've settled on this.
customer_reviews.author: A Buyer

customer_reviews.title: Bang for your buck
customer_reviews.text: Best dog food I’ve tried. I’ve even noticed smaller poops and less gas, which happen with high quality dog food or raw diets.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: High quality product, would recommend
customer_reviews.text: Best food we have found with highest quality ingredients, no pea, potatoes so no worries about enlarged heart, the protein comes from meat, excellent food, dogs love the taste
customer_reviews.author: scott

customer_reviews.title: Good flavor for picky eaters
customer_reviews.text: I have an 80+ lb 10 mth old male Akita who is SUPER picky with his food. He absolutly loves this flavor. Unfortunately he is one who is sensitive to everything. I had to switch him to a more fish based diet which I found out is more inline with what this breed has eaten for many generations. So far he is doing well. If your dog is normal then i highly recommend this dog food.
customer_reviews.author: Jared Hildebrand

customer_reviews.title: My dogs loved it
customer_reviews.text: I haven't been the best owner and have usually gone with the affordable brands that are far from Victor's quality. As soon as I placed it in my dogs bowl they went crazy for it. I will definitely continue to buy this for my dogs.
customer_reviews.author: Julian

customer_reviews.title: Puppy loves this!
customer_reviews.text: The foster mom recommended this for our 3 month old lab. He loves it and the high quality ingredients keep his tummy and bowels happy. Other brands gave him the runs. This doesn’t.
customer_reviews.author: JJB

customer_reviews.title: Not for our picky eater
customer_reviews.text: Highly recommend by other owners of our working breed dog. Sadly, our guy did not like it and refused to eat. We gave it to a friend and their dog loved it. Our guy is very picky.
customer_reviews.author: Katein theCity

customer_reviews.title: I want the best for my fur babies and I did my research ...
customer_reviews.text: Before this I was an avid Blue Buffalo purchaser. I want the best for my fur babies and I did my research and this seems to be a good quality food and is not super expensive like others I have purchased. My dogs eat it, but are not very crazy for it. I am have been purchasing different flavors to see if maybe they prefer another best.
customer_reviews.author: Jen

He's also stopped trying to eat turds, so yeah, this stuff is great! Judging by how much he eats now, he agrees. Also, the small kibble size is perfect for smaller breeds.

customer_reviews.title: Good for Rottweilers
customer_reviews.text: My Frida is a 7 mo Rottweiler. I feed her twice a day and she is getting so big. The food so far is good for her, and I also give it to my 2 Miniature Schnauzers.

customer_reviews.title: GREAT food for my Greyhound
customer_reviews.text: I've struggled finding a good food for my Greyhound. He's a 6 year old retired racer. Victor High Pro Plus firmed up his stool and is extremely affordable! IMPORTANTLY, Victor High Pro Plus received a 5 Star rating on DogFood Advisor.com!!!

customer_reviews.title: Great food and great value!!
customer_reviews.text: This food is excellent and a great value for the money. All dogs do well on this food. No adverse reactions and firm stools. Even picky eaters or the ones with sensitive stomachs do good.
customer_reviews.author: AlyMom

customer_reviews.title: Good
customer_reviews.text: This is what I knew about for our prior dog. Our Dutch shepherd is full and healthy with the minimal feeding. Not a bad batch to date and will continue to buy over chewy.
customer_reviews.author: matt

customer_reviews.title: Recommended by Our Breeder
customer_reviews.text: This is the food recommended by the breeder of our German Shepherd puppy. Our other two dogs also love it. All three are healthy, energetic, have no gastrointestinal issues and are satisfied--no more begging! Very satisfied.
customer_reviews.author: S. L. Gritz

customer_reviews.title: GSD Approved
customer_reviews.text: I have been using this food ever since my K9 trainer fed my German Shepherd during his training. It is incredible kibble and my dog enjoys it. The ingredients do not have the typical garbage of alpo or any of those other "foods" give it a shot!
customer_reviews.author: Etkai

product_meta.title: Victor Classic - Hi-Pro Plus, Dry Dog Food
product_meta.description:
Size:40 lb

One of our top selling formulas, VICTOR Hi-Pro Plus is a nutrient-dense, multi-meat formula packed with high levels of quality protein to support the nutritional needs of growing puppies, pregnant and lactating females, and high-performing dogs. With scientifically advanced and nutritionally complete ingredients, this formula promotes sustained energy and healthy immune and digestive systems.

VICTOR Hi-Pro Plus for Dogs is formulated to meet the nutritional levels established by the AAFCO Dog Food Nutrient Profiles for All Life Stages, except for growth of large size dogs (70 lb. or more as an adult).

CALORIE CONTENT (Calculated ME):

3815 kcal/kg; 406 kcal/cup

GUARANTEED ANALYSIS: 

Crude Protein -------------- 30.0% ( Min.), 
Crude Fat ------------------- 20.0% ( Min.), 
Crude Fiber ----------------- 3.8% ( Max.), 
Moisture -------------------- 9.0% ( Max.), 
Linoleic Acid (Omega 6) --- 2.6% ( Min.), 
Linolenic Acid (Omega 3) -- 0.4% ( Min.), 
DHA ---------------------- 0.1% ( Min.), 
Zinc -------------------- 150 mg/kg ( Min.), 
Selenium -------------- 0.35 mg/kg ( Min.), 
Vitamin E ---------------- 150 IU/kg ( Min.), 
L-Carnitine* ------------- 100 mg/kg ( Min.), 

*Not recognized as an essential nutrient by the AAFCO Dog Food Nutrient Profiles

INGREDIENTS: 

Beef Meal, Grain Sorghum, Chicken Fat (preserved with mixed Tocopherols), Pork Meal, Chicken Meal, Menhaden Fish Meal (source of DHA-Docosahexaenoic Acid), Blood Meal, Whole Grain Millet, Dehydrated Alfalfa Meal, Yeast Culture, Natural Flavor, Potassium Chloride, Carrot Powder, Tomato Pomace (source of Lycopene), Taurine, Salt, Choline Chloride, Dried Seaweed Meal, Zinc Methionine Complex, Vitamin E Supplement, Hydrolyzed Yeast, Iron Amino Acid Complex, Calcium Carbonate, Manganese Amino Acid Complex, Ferrous Sulfate, L-Carnitine, Selenium Yeast, Copper Sulfate, Niacin Supplement, Vitamin B12 Supplement, D-Calcium Pantothenate, Vitamin A Supplement, Thiamine Mononitrate, Biotin, Riboflavin Supplement, Calcium Iodate, Pyridoxine Hydrochloride, Vitamin D3 Supplement, Powdered Cellulose, Brewers Dried Yeast, Dried Enterococcus Faecium Fermentation Product, Dried Aspergillus Oryzae Fermentation Extract, Dried Trichoderma Longibrachiatum Fermentation Extract, Dried Bacillus Subtilis Fermentation Extract, Silicon Dioxide, Tetra Sodium Pyrophosphate, Vegetable Oil, Rosemary Extract, Green Tea Extract, Spearmint Extract, Lecithin, Fructooligosaccharide, Folic Acid, Yucca Schidigera Extract.

FEEDING GUIDELINES: 

Refer to Recommended Feeding Chart for Adult Dogs. 
Number of Cups Per Day (8 oz measuring cup) 

5 lbs. -------- ½ cup 
10 lbs. ------ ⅞ cup 
15 lbs. ------1 ¼ cups 
20 lbs. ------ 1 ½ cups 
30 lbs. ------ 2 cups 
40 lbs. ------ 2 ½ cups 
60 lbs. ------ 3 ⅓ cups 
80 lbs. ------ 4 cups 
100 lbs. ----- 4 ⅞ cups

FEEDING PUPPIES:

Puppies will typically start nibbling moistened dog foods at 3 to 4 weeks of age. Feed as much as the puppy will eat in 20 minutes in 4 feeding intervals spaced throughout the day. May be mixed with water, broth or milk at a ratio of 3 parts food to 1 part liquid. To ensure product freshness, do not leave moistened food out for more than 30 minutes. Puppies will be weaned from milk by 3 weeks of age. Continue to feed up to 4 times per day. Within a few months, the puppies may be transitioned to a self-feeder. After age one, feed to maintain good body condition, using the feeding chart as a guide.

PREGNANCY AND NURSING:

Energy requirements continually change during stages of gestation and lactation and may require up to four times recommended levels of intake. Adjust amount of food provided to maintain good body condition of your female dog.

TIPS ON TRANSITIONING TO VICTOR:

When changing from a different food to any VICTOR dog food formula, transition your dog to VICTOR over the course of one week to 10 days, gradually increasing the amount of VICTOR every few days.

Keep fresh water available at all times.

Excellent for dogs that need high levels of quality protein, like growing puppies and pregnant or nursing females
Fortified with vitamins, minerals, essential fatty acids, protein and amino acids
Formulated with our scientifically advanced, proven VICTOR Core ingredients to promote healthy immune and digestive systems.
Superior digestibility aids in less food intake for a better pound-for-pound value. Made from gluten free grains.
